President Muhammadu Buhari has appointed Mohammad Nami to replace the Chairman of the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS), Babatunde Fowler. Fowler, according to a statement by the Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Mallam Garba Shehu, has been directed to hand over to the most senior director on the FIRS board. The President also approved the composition of a new board for FIRS subject to Senate confirmation. Fowler’s tenure of four years, though renewable at the discretion of the President, expired on Monday. More Details Later… President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday appointed Dr. William Babatunde Fowler as the Executive Chairman of the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS). August 20, 2015 In "News" Emma Ujah There is palpable anxiety among management and senior staff of the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS) as the four-year tenure of the Executive Chairman, Mr Tunde Fowler ended yesterday without a word from the Presidency. Fowler's tenure is renewable but there has not been any movement in that… December 9, 2019 In "News" By Levinus Nwabughiogu ABUJA - Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) Comrade Timi Frank on Tuesday stated that the new the Executive Chairman of the Board of the Federal Inland Revenue Service (FIRS), Dr. William Babatunde Fowler has flagrantly disobeyed the law by assuming office… October 7, 2015 In "News"